WEBVTT

03:43.807 --> 03:45.224
Dad.

05:30.914 --> 05:35.167
Clear the ramp! 30 seconds!
God be with you!

05:35.252 --> 05:40.506
Port side stick, starboard side stick,
move fast and clear those murder holes.

05:40.590 --> 05:42.925
l want to see plenty of beach
between men.

05:43.009 --> 05:46.929
Five men is a juicy opportunity.
One man is a waste of ammo.

05:47.013 --> 05:49.098
Keep the sand out of your weapons.

05:49.224 --> 05:53.602
Keep those actions clear.
And l'll see you on the beach.

06:25.761 --> 06:27.970
Clear the murder holes!

06:44.321 --> 06:45.863
Over the side!

06:52.370 --> 06:54.789
Port and starboard, over...

08:03.984 --> 08:05.234
Jesus.

08:05.694 --> 08:07.444
Thank you...

10:26.334 --> 10:29.378
l said, what the hell do we do now, sir?

10:30.839 --> 10:34.049
Captain Miller! Captain Miller!

10:35.719 --> 10:38.887
-Captain Miller!
-Sergeant Horvath!

10:40.432 --> 10:44.101
Move your men off the beach! Go!

10:44.227 --> 10:45.519
Okay, you guys!

10:45.603 --> 10:48.689
-Get on my ass! Follow me!
-Sir!

10:49.065 --> 10:51.066
What's the rallying point?

10:51.192 --> 10:52.985
Anywhere but here!

11:06.082 --> 11:08.542
The seawall! Move up to the seawall!

11:08.626 --> 11:10.919
Sir, l'm staying!

11:11.004 --> 11:13.297
Clear this beach!
Make way for the others!

11:13.423 --> 11:15.966
This is all we got
between us and the Almighty.

11:16.092 --> 11:20.095
Every inch of this beach
has been pre-sighted!

11:20.972 --> 11:24.266
You stay here, you're dead men!

11:37.489 --> 11:41.033
Mama! Mama!

11:45.663 --> 11:48.165
Stay down! Stay down!

11:52.837 --> 11:54.171
What are you guys?

11:54.255 --> 11:56.965
1 04th Medical Battalion, sir!

11:57.050 --> 11:59.718
Here to set up field operations!

11:59.803 --> 12:01.345
Get rid of that crap!

12:01.429 --> 12:04.515
Grab yourselves some weapons.
Follow me.

12:12.107 --> 12:15.025
-l'm hit! l'm hit!
-Briggs!

12:19.280 --> 12:23.575
Get me out of here. l'm hit low. God!

12:23.660 --> 12:26.745
-Medic!
-Navy Beach Battalion, sir.

12:26.830 --> 12:30.541
l gotta clear these obstacles,
make holes for the tanks.

12:30.625 --> 12:32.960
All the armour is foundering
in the Channel.

12:33.044 --> 12:36.296
Orders, sir. You go somewhere else.
l'm clearing this one!

12:36.381 --> 12:38.173
Come on, Briggs!

12:42.762 --> 12:44.138
Medic!

13:21.217 --> 13:22.843
Move! Move!

13:30.518 --> 13:33.645
Move! Come on! Move!

13:55.418 --> 13:58.754
Shore party.
No armour has made it ashore.

13:58.838 --> 14:03.550
We got no DD tanks on the beach.
Dog One is not open.

14:04.510 --> 14:08.138
-Who's in command here?
-You are, sir!

14:09.766 --> 14:12.226
-Sergeant Horvath!
-Sir!

14:12.310 --> 14:14.353
You recognise where we are?

14:14.437 --> 14:16.855
Right where we're supposed to be,
but no one else is!

14:16.940 --> 14:20.400
Nobody's where they're supposed to be.

14:20.485 --> 14:22.069
Shore party.

14:22.862 --> 14:25.113
First wave, ineffective.

14:25.198 --> 14:29.243
We do not hold the beach.
Say again, we do not hold the beach.

14:29.619 --> 14:30.994
We're all mixed up, sir.

14:31.079 --> 14:32.871
We got the leftovers from Fox Company,

14:32.956 --> 14:34.915
Able Company and George Company!

14:34.999 --> 14:38.627
Plus we got some Navy demo guys
and a beachmaster!

14:40.171 --> 14:43.173
Shore party. Shore party.

14:49.264 --> 14:51.598
CATF , CATF ...

14:55.103 --> 14:57.396
-Reiben here, sir!
-Did you see anybody else?

14:57.480 --> 15:00.274
-Jackson, but that's about it.
-Mellish here.

15:00.358 --> 15:03.610
Caparzo! We got DeForest
back there with Wade.

15:03.695 --> 15:07.447
He's hurt so bad he says
he sprung 1 00 leaks.

15:07.532 --> 15:09.199
Wade says he's all used up.

15:09.284 --> 15:11.535
-Move on to somebody you can help.
-Let's go!

15:11.619 --> 15:14.079
He's battalion surgeon, sir!

15:18.126 --> 15:20.085
-Get his attention.
-Wade!

15:20.169 --> 15:21.670
-Yo, Doc!
-Wade!

15:21.754 --> 15:24.923
-Wade! Wade! Wade!
-Wade!

15:25.967 --> 15:29.261
-Wade! Wade! Wade!
-Too risky, Doc. Too risky.

15:30.722 --> 15:32.806
-Wade!
-All right. Get him off the beach.

15:32.890 --> 15:36.643
l got it! We stopped the bleeding!
We stopped the bleeding!

15:38.187 --> 15:39.813
Fuck!

15:39.897 --> 15:43.191
Just give us a fucking chance,
you son of a bitch!

15:43.276 --> 15:45.694
-Son of a fucking cocksucker!
-Wade! Come on. Come on.

15:45.778 --> 15:48.989
Wade! lt's Mellish! Wade!

15:49.532 --> 15:51.199
-Mellish!
-Let's go!

15:51.284 --> 15:52.451
We found Miller!

15:52.535 --> 15:55.120
-Fuck it!
-Let's move! Let's move!

16:02.170 --> 16:05.297
This is all? This is all that's made it?

16:05.381 --> 16:08.884
We got scattered pretty bad, sir.
There's bound to be more.

16:09.886 --> 16:12.220
-Not enough. lt's not enough.
-Dog One exit...

16:12.305 --> 16:13.680
lt's gotta be that cut on the right.

16:13.765 --> 16:16.266
-Or is that one on the left? Shit!
-No. No, no, no.

16:16.351 --> 16:19.061
Vierville is to the west of us.
This is Dog One.

16:19.145 --> 16:20.395
They're killing us!

16:20.480 --> 16:24.608
And we don't have a fucking chance,
and that ain't fair!

16:24.692 --> 16:28.987
Gather weapons and ammo!

16:29.072 --> 16:32.157
Come on, let's drag them in
off the sand!

16:40.249 --> 16:44.169
Reiben. Hey, Reiben, Reiben, Reiben,
where's your BAR?

16:44.921 --> 16:47.047
Bottom of the channel, sir.
The bitch tried to drown me.

16:47.131 --> 16:49.007
Find a replacement.

16:51.052 --> 16:54.012
Bangalores! Bring up some bangalores!

16:55.431 --> 16:58.975
Grenades, grenades! Get me
some grenades. Get them over here!

17:01.646 --> 17:05.648
Bangalores up the line!
Bangalores up the line!

17:05.733 --> 17:08.026
Heads up! Bangers coming your way!

17:08.111 --> 17:10.529
Come on, come on, come on!

17:10.613 --> 17:13.448
-Jackson here, sir!
-Reiben back, sir!

17:14.117 --> 17:16.867
Oh, my God!

17:19.872 --> 17:22.332
One more. Give me one more.

17:27.672 --> 17:30.382
Oh, my God, it hurts! l'm gonna die!

17:30.466 --> 17:34.428
Oh, my God! Oh, Jesus! Oh, my God!

17:35.555 --> 17:38.974
Keep it moving. Keep it moving.
Almost got it.

17:39.058 --> 17:42.102
-Jesus! Lucky bastard.
-Come on.

17:42.979 --> 17:45.272
-Move it!
-Keep it moving. You got it?

17:45.356 --> 17:48.400
God! God, help me!

17:49.026 --> 17:50.944
You're not gonna die.
You're not gonna die.

17:51.028 --> 17:54.197
You're fine. Don't look at it.
Don't look at it.

17:54.282 --> 17:58.034
Bangalores! Clear the shingle!

17:58.119 --> 18:00.787
-Fire in the hole!
-Fire in the hole!

18:00.872 --> 18:06.334
Fire in the hole!

18:15.928 --> 18:19.639
We're in business! Defilade!
Other side of the hole!

18:32.695 --> 18:35.030
That's it! Let's go!

18:38.493 --> 18:40.619
lnspected. Morphine.

18:43.498 --> 18:44.873
Routine.

18:50.880 --> 18:52.339
Priority.

18:56.344 --> 18:57.552
He's gone.

19:09.982 --> 19:11.733
Son of a...

19:12.485 --> 19:15.153
-Get in there.
-Fuck. l can't move.

19:15.238 --> 19:16.488
-Mellish.
-Yes, sir.

19:16.572 --> 19:18.406
Give me your bayonet.

19:38.594 --> 19:42.347
Two MG42s and two mortars.
Add 20, left 30.

19:45.434 --> 19:48.186
There's a little defilade over there,
but it's the perfect fire position

19:48.271 --> 19:50.021
if we get some goddamn armour
on the beach.

19:50.106 --> 19:53.191
We gotta open up this draw!
We gotta get this draw open.

19:53.276 --> 19:55.193
Reiben, Mellish, let's get into the war!

19:55.278 --> 19:58.280
Grab some cover
and put some fire on that crew.

19:58.364 --> 20:02.075
Davis, Debernardo,
Young, Valk, get ready.

20:04.412 --> 20:06.121
Covering fire!

20:09.458 --> 20:11.167
Go, go, go!

20:25.182 --> 20:27.142
Goddamn firing squad.

20:27.268 --> 20:30.437
lt's the only way we can get
everybody the hell out of here.

20:30.521 --> 20:34.733
Short, Payton, McDonald, Parkes!
You're next!

20:34.817 --> 20:37.444
Why don't we just hand out
blindfolds, Cap?

20:37.528 --> 20:39.112
All we can do here is die.

20:39.196 --> 20:40.780
Covering fire!

20:43.284 --> 20:45.035
Go, go, go!

20:46.287 --> 20:47.996
Come on! Come on! Come on!

20:48.122 --> 20:49.998
Go, God damn it!

21:02.345 --> 21:05.013
-Jackson.
-Sir.

21:06.223 --> 21:07.807
-Do you see that impact crater?
-Yes, sir.

21:07.892 --> 21:10.268
That should give you complete defilade
from that machine-gun position.

21:10.353 --> 21:12.228
Get in there and give me
some fire discipline.

21:12.355 --> 21:14.230
Wait for my command.

21:19.987 --> 21:21.363
Go!

21:32.416 --> 21:35.710
Captain, if your mother saw you do that,
she'd be very upset.

21:35.836 --> 21:38.088
l thought you were my mother.

21:38.923 --> 21:41.675
Be not thou far from me, O Lord.

21:46.222 --> 21:50.225
O my God, l am heartily sorry
for having offended thee.

21:51.435 --> 21:53.687
l detest my sins
for having offended thee, O Lord.

21:53.771 --> 21:55.313
l detest my sins for having
offended thee, O Lord.

21:55.398 --> 21:57.440
Listen to me, Lord.

22:02.697 --> 22:06.282
All my strength, haste thee to help me.

22:22.091 --> 22:27.095
-Dog One exit! Right here!
-We're in business!

22:28.639 --> 22:30.473
Move! Move!

23:11.807 --> 23:13.433
-Reiben.
-Let's go, Sarge. Go!

23:13.517 --> 23:14.809
Reiben.

23:39.668 --> 23:42.128
The place is full of 'em!

23:43.672 --> 23:45.340
Come on, Doyle!

23:46.842 --> 23:48.259
Sarge?

23:53.599 --> 23:56.684
-Flame!
-Doyle, do it!

24:01.190 --> 24:03.858
Don't shoot! Let them burn!

24:25.840 --> 24:29.133
l'll give you "comrade,"
you son of a bitch!

24:29.218 --> 24:30.885
Lie down!

24:59.081 --> 25:01.583
Cease fire! Cease fire!

25:01.667 --> 25:04.836
Cut it out! Cut it out! Cease fire!

25:05.921 --> 25:07.589
Sugar Cane. Sugar Charlie 3.

25:07.715 --> 25:10.925
Say again, Dog One is open.
Send in the dozers.

25:11.051 --> 25:14.095
l'm waiting for you
to tie in my flanks. Over.

25:15.097 --> 25:16.598
What?

25:19.184 --> 25:22.520
What? l'm sorry, l can't understand
what you're saying.

25:30.446 --> 25:33.031
What did he say? What did he say?

25:33.115 --> 25:36.284
"Look, l washed for supper."

25:40.915 --> 25:42.415
God damn it!

25:48.797 --> 25:50.381
-Hey, Fish.
-Yeah?

25:50.466 --> 25:53.134
Look at this. A Hitler Youth knife.

25:54.637 --> 25:57.805
And now
it's a Shabbat challah cutter, right?

26:07.733 --> 26:09.400
Keep it moving!

27:09.586 --> 27:11.462
That's quite a view.

27:12.423 --> 27:13.965
Yes, it is.

27:15.676 --> 27:17.218
Quite a view.

28:52.022 --> 28:54.190
"Dear Mr Brian Boyd,

28:54.274 --> 28:56.442
"no doubt by now you have
received full information..."

28:56.527 --> 28:58.736
-"Dear Mrs Jensen..."
-"...untimely death of your son."

28:58.821 --> 29:00.738
"...no words of mine
can ever relieve the grief..."

29:00.823 --> 29:03.116
"Our outfit has felt his loss
tremendously."

29:03.200 --> 29:05.952
"He was a fine soldier
and he believed very strongly in..."

29:06.036 --> 29:08.746
"lt's no secret any more
that we were involved

29:08.831 --> 29:10.915
"in one of the most important
operations of this war."

29:10.999 --> 29:13.543
"Al was the one
who held us all together.

29:13.627 --> 29:14.877
"He was always the first to volunteer..."

29:14.962 --> 29:18.589
"...came to a clearing near a road
where over 4,000 troops had passed..."

29:18.674 --> 29:20.883
"Your husband served in a combat unit

29:20.968 --> 29:23.511
"whose dangerous duty
is to place itself..."

29:23.595 --> 29:26.722
"...which we all cherish
and hold so dear.

29:26.807 --> 29:30.518
"The loss of Lee and others like him
is a distinct blow to the regiment."

29:30.602 --> 29:31.894
"l fully understand your desire

29:31.979 --> 29:34.647
"to learn as much as possible
regarding the circumstances

29:34.731 --> 29:36.858
"leading to his death."

30:29.036 --> 30:30.786
Colonel, l've got something
you should know about.

30:30.871 --> 30:32.163
Yes.

30:34.166 --> 30:36.709
These two men died in Normandy.

30:37.336 --> 30:40.171
This one at Omaha Beach.

30:40.255 --> 30:43.716
-Sean Ryan.
-This man at Utah.

30:45.385 --> 30:47.094
Peter Ryan.

30:50.849 --> 30:53.935
This man was killed
last week in New Guinea.

30:56.688 --> 30:59.106
Daniel Ryan.

30:59.816 --> 31:01.734
The three men are brothers, sir.

31:01.818 --> 31:03.277
l've just learned that, this afternoon,

31:03.362 --> 31:07.156
their mother is going
to be getting all three telegrams.

31:10.118 --> 31:12.370
That's not all. There's a fourth brother.
The youngest.

31:12.454 --> 31:14.455
He parachuted in
with the 1 01 st Airborne,

31:14.539 --> 31:15.998
night before the invasion.

31:16.083 --> 31:17.917
He's somewhere in Normandy.
We don't know where.

31:18.001 --> 31:20.419
-ls he alive?
-We don't know.

31:24.591 --> 31:26.217
Come with me.

33:10.030 --> 33:12.406
God damn it.

33:13.241 --> 33:15.076
All four of them
were in the same company

33:15.160 --> 33:17.161
in the 29th Division,
but we split them up

33:17.245 --> 33:19.038
after the Sullivan brothers died
on the Juneau.

33:21.041 --> 33:22.875
Any contact with the fourth son, James?

33:22.959 --> 33:26.921
No, sir. He was dropped about
1 5 miles inland near Neuville.

33:27.005 --> 33:28.297
But that's still deep
behind German lines.

33:28.382 --> 33:30.591
Now, Mac,
there is no way you can know

33:30.675 --> 33:33.594
where in the hell he was dropped.

33:33.678 --> 33:35.638
General, first reports out of
lke's people at SHAEF

33:35.722 --> 33:37.598
said the 1 01 st is scattered
all to hell and gone.

33:37.682 --> 33:40.059
There's misdrops all over Normandy.

33:40.143 --> 33:43.062
Now, assuming Private Ryan
even survived the jump,

33:43.146 --> 33:44.605
he could be anywhere.

33:44.689 --> 33:46.732
ln fact, he's probably KlA.

33:46.817 --> 33:50.486
And frankly, sir, we go sending
some sort of rescue mission,

33:50.570 --> 33:53.155
flathatting throughout swarms
of German reinforcements

33:53.240 --> 33:57.076
all along our axis of advance,
they're gonna be KlA, too.

34:19.599 --> 34:21.641
l have a letter here,

34:23.018 --> 34:27.106
written a long time ago
to a Mrs Bixby in Boston.

34:27.190 --> 34:29.108
So bear with me.

34:31.945 --> 34:33.487
"Dear Madam,

34:34.197 --> 34:36.449
"l have been shown in the files
of the War Department

34:36.533 --> 34:40.286
"a statement of the Adjutant
General of Massachusetts

34:40.370 --> 34:43.706
"that you are the mother of five

34:46.710 --> 34:50.420
"sons who have died gloriously
on the field of battle.

34:53.091 --> 34:56.844
"l feel how weak and fruitless
must be any words of mine

34:57.637 --> 35:01.015
"that would attempt
to beguile you from the grief

35:01.433 --> 35:03.851
"of a loss so overwhelming.

35:05.687 --> 35:07.688
"But l cannot refrain
from tendering to you

35:07.772 --> 35:10.941
"the consolation that may be found

35:11.026 --> 35:15.279
"in the thanks of the republic
they died to save.

35:19.451 --> 35:20.743
"l pray that Our Heavenly Father

35:20.827 --> 35:23.913
"may assuage the anguish
of your bereavement

35:23.997 --> 35:28.375
"and leave you only the cherished
memory of the loved lost,

35:29.503 --> 35:31.128
"and the solemn pride
that must be yours

35:31.213 --> 35:35.508
"to have laid so costly a sacrifice
upon the altar of freedom.

35:36.092 --> 35:39.261
"Yours very sincerely and respectfully,

35:39.346 --> 35:41.180
"Abraham Lincoln."

36:00.033 --> 36:01.867
That boy is alive.

36:02.577 --> 36:05.496
We are gonna send somebody
to find him,

36:06.623 --> 36:09.792
and we are gonna get him
the hell out of there.

36:10.835 --> 36:12.503
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

36:25.183 --> 36:27.643
We expected 32 tanks to float to
the beach. Twenty-seven didn't make it.

36:27.727 --> 36:29.770
-Miller, Charlie Company.
-Go on in, Captain.

36:29.854 --> 36:30.980
l understand your situation.

36:31.064 --> 36:34.149
But if we don't offload
those duel-drive Shermans by 0600,

36:34.234 --> 36:35.442
we're gonna have an entire division

36:35.527 --> 36:39.238
stuck at Carentan
with its pants around its ankles.

36:39.322 --> 36:41.740
Well, you let me know then.

36:41.825 --> 36:44.702
Have Charlie Company hold at Vierville
until we can get some armour up there.

36:44.786 --> 36:46.620
Yes, sir. Runner!

36:53.086 --> 36:55.838
Airborne was supposed to win
an open door for the rest of us.

36:55.922 --> 36:58.507
lnstead they misdropped,
scattered all their sticks into the wind.

36:58.592 --> 37:02.761
-What's your situation?
-Yes, sir. Sector four is secure.

37:03.138 --> 37:04.388
We...

37:04.973 --> 37:10.060
We took out towed 88s
here, here and here.

37:10.145 --> 37:11.812
They'd already gotten four
of our Shermans

37:11.896 --> 37:13.188
and a number
of our deuce and a halves.

37:13.273 --> 37:16.233
These two minefields
are actually one big one.

37:16.318 --> 37:17.985
We tried to make our way up
through the middle of it,

37:18.069 --> 37:20.446
but it turned into a mixed,
high-density field,

37:20.530 --> 37:21.655
little bit of everything.

37:21.740 --> 37:25.576
Spreng Mine 44s. Schuh Mine 42s,
pot mines. A-200s,

37:25.660 --> 37:29.163
the little wooden bastards
that the mine detectors don't pick up.

37:29.247 --> 37:33.709
This road here, they placed
big mushrooms, Teller Mine 43s,

37:33.793 --> 37:34.960
l guess for our tanks,

37:35.045 --> 37:38.547
from here right up
to the edge of the village. Right here.

37:38.632 --> 37:40.591
So we marked them,
called the engineers.

37:40.675 --> 37:41.967
Resistance?

37:42.052 --> 37:44.261
We had higher
support expectations, sir.

37:44.346 --> 37:46.639
There was an under-strength
company without artillery.

37:46.723 --> 37:49.975
Wehrmacht 346 lnfantry,
Von Luck Kampfgruppe.

37:50.060 --> 37:52.102
We ended up with 23 prisoners.

37:52.187 --> 37:55.356
We turned them over
to MPs from the 29th.

37:58.109 --> 38:00.402
What about our casualties?

38:01.029 --> 38:03.155
Well, the figures

38:04.532 --> 38:08.035
were 35 dead, times two wounded.

38:08.119 --> 38:11.372
They just didn't wanna
give up those 88s.

38:13.291 --> 38:16.043
lt was a tough assignment.
That's why you got it.

38:16.127 --> 38:17.628
Yes, sir.

38:18.880 --> 38:20.381
John...

38:23.343 --> 38:25.260
l've got another one for you.

38:25.345 --> 38:28.305
-Yes, sir.
-This one's straight from the top.

38:34.896 --> 38:37.064
You and l are taking a squad
over to Neuville

38:37.148 --> 38:39.066
on a public-relations mission.

38:39.150 --> 38:40.984
You leading a squad?

38:41.069 --> 38:44.196
Some private in the 1 01 st
lost three brothers,

38:44.280 --> 38:45.948
and he's got a ticket home.

38:46.032 --> 38:47.157
How come Neuville?

38:47.242 --> 38:51.161
They think he's up there somewhere,
part of all those airborne misdrops.

38:51.246 --> 38:53.956
lt's not gonna be easy
finding one particular soldier

38:54.040 --> 38:55.207
in the middle of this
whole goddamn war.

38:55.291 --> 38:57.751
Like finding a needle
in a stack of needles.

38:57.836 --> 38:59.420
But what about the company?

38:59.504 --> 39:02.798
We take the pick of the litter
and the rest get folded into Baker.

39:02.882 --> 39:04.591
Jesus Christ.

39:04.676 --> 39:06.719
They took away your company?

39:06.803 --> 39:11.306
lt wasn't my company. lt was
the Army's. So they told me, anyway.

39:11.433 --> 39:15.352
Give me Reiben on BAR, Jackson,
Wade, Beasley and Caparzo.

39:15.437 --> 39:16.854
Beasley's dead.

39:16.938 --> 39:19.732
All right, Mellish, then.
We got anybody speaks French?

39:19.816 --> 39:23.652
-Not that l know of.
-What about Talbot?

39:23.778 --> 39:26.780
-This morning.
-Oh. All right.

39:27.198 --> 39:29.283
l'm gonna go try to dig up
another interpreter.

39:29.367 --> 39:31.118
Assemble at battalion motor pool
on the beach.

39:31.202 --> 39:32.286
Yes, sir.

39:32.370 --> 39:33.746
-Sarge, what we gonna do?
-Okay, listen up...

39:33.830 --> 39:35.205
-What?
-What are we gonna do?

39:35.290 --> 39:36.999
You're going home wrapped
in an American flag

39:37.125 --> 39:39.126
with a hunk of cheese
in your ass, Caparzo, you smart ass.

39:39.210 --> 39:40.961
-Now, listen up.
-l thought you liked it in the ass.

39:41.045 --> 39:42.379
-What?
-l thought you liked it in the ass.

39:43.047 --> 39:45.174
Attention!

39:45.300 --> 39:46.508
As you were.

39:46.634 --> 39:48.677
l'm looking
for Corporal Upham, Timothy E.

39:48.803 --> 39:50.095
Yes, sir. l'm Upham, sir.

39:50.180 --> 39:51.805
l understand you speak
French and German.

39:51.890 --> 39:53.682
-Yes, sir.
-How's your accent?

39:53.808 --> 39:55.434
Just a slight one in French,
but my German's clean.

39:55.518 --> 39:57.186
-Has a touch of Bavarian, sir.
-Very good.

39:57.312 --> 39:58.854
You've been reassigned to me.
Grab your gear.

39:58.980 --> 40:01.315
-We're going to a place called Neuville.
-Yes, sir.

40:01.399 --> 40:03.567
-When was this updated?
-Updated as of 0830 hour this morning.

40:03.651 --> 40:05.903
-Sir...
-This is the 1 2th SS Panzer.

40:05.987 --> 40:07.821
These are the two axes
that advance south.

40:07.906 --> 40:10.365
-Sir, there are Germans in Neuville.
-There are artillery up here, sir.

40:10.492 --> 40:13.160
-That's what l understand. Corporal.
-Yes, sir.

40:13.244 --> 40:15.412
Sir, there are a lot
of Germans in Neuville.

40:15.497 --> 40:16.580
You have a problem with that, Corporal?

40:16.664 --> 40:19.124
No, sir. Just if you consider
l've never been in combat, sir.

40:19.209 --> 40:20.834
l make maps and l translate.
And that's...

40:20.919 --> 40:23.837
l need someone who speaks
French and German.

40:23.922 --> 40:25.672
-Yes, sir.
-My two guys were killed.

40:25.757 --> 40:28.425
Yes, sir. lt's just that l haven't
held a weapon since basic training, sir.

40:28.510 --> 40:31.136
Did you fire the weapon
in basic training?

40:31.221 --> 40:32.429
Yes, sir.

40:32.514 --> 40:35.265
-Well, then, get your gear.
-Yes, sir.

40:36.392 --> 40:38.685
Sir, may l bring...

40:42.440 --> 40:44.942
May l bring my typewriter, sir?

40:50.031 --> 40:51.365
Yes, sir.

40:54.619 --> 40:56.411
Thank you very much, sir.

40:56.538 --> 40:58.872
-That a souvenir?
-No, sir.

40:58.957 --> 41:01.124
Take your time, Corporal.

41:05.463 --> 41:08.006
You should look
on the bright side of things, Corporal.

41:08.091 --> 41:09.216
Yes, sir.

41:09.300 --> 41:12.344
For one thing,
you don't need to carry those.

41:12.428 --> 41:15.389
-You'll need that.
-l'll need that, sir. Yes, sir.

42:13.990 --> 42:15.365
Hey.

42:15.450 --> 42:17.618
You want your head blown off,
you fancy little fuck?

42:17.702 --> 42:19.995
Don't you ever fucking touch me
with those little rat claws again.

42:20.121 --> 42:22.623
Get the fuck back in formation.

42:24.000 --> 42:27.502
l was just wondering
where you're from, that's...

42:32.550 --> 42:34.968
-Caparzo, is it?
-Hey, drop dead, Corporal.

42:35.053 --> 42:36.178
Got you.

42:36.304 --> 42:38.472
And another thing.
Every time you salute the captain,

42:38.556 --> 42:40.766
you make him a target for the Germans.

42:40.850 --> 42:42.643
So do us a favour. Don't do it.

42:42.727 --> 42:45.687
Especially when l'm standing
next to him, capisci?

42:46.522 --> 42:48.815
Corporal, what's your book about?

42:48.900 --> 42:50.609
-Hey. Watch your rifle.
-Sorry.

42:50.693 --> 42:51.944
Actually, it's about the...

42:52.028 --> 42:53.487
lt's supposed to be about
the bonds of brotherhood

42:53.571 --> 42:55.489
that develop between
soldiers during war.

42:55.573 --> 42:57.658
Brotherhood?

42:57.742 --> 42:59.326
What do you know about brotherhood?

42:59.410 --> 43:01.536
Get a load of this guy, Fish.

43:01.663 --> 43:04.623
Why don't you ask
the captain where he's from?

43:04.707 --> 43:09.086
Yeah, ask the captain. He'll tell you
everything you wanna know about him.

43:09.253 --> 43:11.338
You wanna explain
the math of this to me?

43:11.422 --> 43:13.715
l mean, where's the sense
of risking the lives of the eight of us

43:13.841 --> 43:15.384
to save one guy.

43:15.510 --> 43:18.637
Twenty degrees.
Anybody wanna answer that?

43:18.721 --> 43:22.265
Reiben, think about
the poor bastard's mother.

43:22.350 --> 43:24.142
Hey, doc. l got a mother, all right?

43:24.227 --> 43:26.770
l mean, you got a mother.
Sarge has got a mother.

43:26.854 --> 43:30.524
l mean, shit, l bet even
the captain's got a mother.

43:30.608 --> 43:33.443
Well, maybe not the captain,
but the rest of us got mothers.

43:33.528 --> 43:37.197
"Theirs not to reason why
Theirs but to do and die"

43:38.574 --> 43:40.367
What the fuck is that
supposed to mean, Corporal, huh?

43:40.451 --> 43:42.119
We're all supposed to die. ls that it?

43:42.203 --> 43:44.955
Upham's talking about
our duty as soldiers.

43:45.039 --> 43:47.541
-Yes, sir.
-We all have orders we have to follow.

43:47.625 --> 43:50.335
And that supersedes everything,
including your mothers.

43:50.420 --> 43:52.004
Yes, sir. Thank you, sir.

43:52.088 --> 43:54.506
Even if you think
the mission's FUBAR, sir?

43:54.590 --> 43:57.592
Especially if you think
the mission's FUBAR.

43:57.719 --> 44:01.388
-What's FUBAR?
-Oh, it's German. Yeah.

44:01.973 --> 44:04.057
Never heard of that.

44:04.142 --> 44:07.436
Sir, l have an opinion on this matter.

44:08.229 --> 44:11.148
Well, by all means,
share it with the squad.

44:11.232 --> 44:13.442
Well, from my way of thinking, sir,

44:13.568 --> 44:15.902
this entire mission
is a serious misallocation

44:15.987 --> 44:18.405
of valuable military resources.

44:18.489 --> 44:20.407
Yeah. Go on.

44:20.491 --> 44:22.951
Well, it seems to me, sir,
that God gave me a special gift,

44:23.077 --> 44:26.329
made me a fine instrument of warfare.

44:26.414 --> 44:29.124
Reiben, pay attention.
Now, this is the way to gripe!

44:29.250 --> 44:30.500
Continue, Jackson.

44:30.585 --> 44:32.461
Well, what l mean by that, sir,

44:32.587 --> 44:35.255
is if you was to put me
and this here sniper rifle anywhere,

44:35.339 --> 44:38.091
up to and including one mile
ofAdolf Hitler

44:38.176 --> 44:39.885
with a clear line of sight, sir...

44:39.969 --> 44:42.846
Pack your bags, fellas.
War's over. Amen.

44:42.930 --> 44:45.223
Oh, that's brilliant, bumpkin.

44:45.308 --> 44:48.351
So, Captain, what about you?
l mean, you don't gripe at all?

44:48.436 --> 44:50.854
l don't gripe to you, Reiben.
l'm a captain.

44:50.938 --> 44:53.857
There's a chain of command.
Gripes go up, not down. Always up.

44:53.941 --> 44:55.233
You gripe to me,

44:55.318 --> 44:58.862
l gripe to my superior officers,
so on, so on and so on.

44:58.946 --> 45:00.739
l don't gripe to you.
l don't gripe in front of you.

45:00.823 --> 45:02.824
You should know that as a Ranger.

45:02.950 --> 45:04.785
l'm sorry, sir, but...

45:04.869 --> 45:07.704
Let's say you weren't a captain,
or maybe l was a major.

45:07.789 --> 45:09.581
What would you say then?

45:09.665 --> 45:11.458
Well, in that case,

45:11.542 --> 45:13.627
l'd say this is an excellent mission, sir,

45:13.711 --> 45:16.838
with an extremely
valuable objective, sir,

45:16.964 --> 45:18.381
worthy of my best efforts, sir.

45:18.466 --> 45:23.970
Moreover, l feel heartfelt sorrow
for the mother of Private James Ryan,

45:24.055 --> 45:27.599
and am willing to lay down my life
and the lives of my men,

45:27.683 --> 45:31.144
especially you, Reiben,
to ease her suffering.

45:32.647 --> 45:34.648
-He's good.
-l love him.

45:45.326 --> 45:46.701
Right.

46:28.578 --> 46:31.788
-Thunder!
-Flash!

46:31.873 --> 46:35.125
Upham, over there. Reiben, you four go.

46:44.594 --> 46:46.636
Go, go, go, go, go!

46:51.976 --> 46:54.936
-You guys are a sight for sore eyes.
-Sergeant Hill, our relief showed up.

46:55.021 --> 46:56.813
How many are you?

46:56.898 --> 46:59.524
Just eight of us.
We're not your relief. Sorry.

46:59.609 --> 47:01.151
You're not the relief,
what do you mean, sir?

47:01.235 --> 47:02.819
We're here for a Private Ryan.

47:02.904 --> 47:05.447
Who? Ryan? What for?

47:05.531 --> 47:06.656
-ls he here?
-Well, l don't know.

47:06.741 --> 47:09.034
Maybe with a mixed unit
on the other side of town.

47:09.118 --> 47:11.203
lt's hard to get to. The Germans
punched a hole in our centre

47:11.287 --> 47:13.163
a few hours ago,
they cut us right in two.

47:13.247 --> 47:16.750
-What's his name again?
-Ryan. James Ryan.

47:16.834 --> 47:18.210
He dropped in with 1 01 st.

47:18.294 --> 47:21.254
-Goldman, get me a runner up here.
-Runner!

47:21.339 --> 47:23.006
Come on.

47:26.969 --> 47:29.554
Jonesy, make a hole up there!

47:31.098 --> 47:34.226
We got stopped by some intense
rifle action from the eastward.

47:34.310 --> 47:38.021
The Germans have been
reinforcing two regiments all day.

47:38.105 --> 47:40.315
The streets have been quiet
for about 45 minutes.

47:40.399 --> 47:42.901
Most of the German fire now
is concentrated to the westward.

47:42.985 --> 47:44.194
Who's that on the loudspeaker?

47:44.278 --> 47:46.279
That? That's Dagwood Dusseldorf,

47:46.364 --> 47:48.198
our friendly neighbourhood
morale officer.

47:48.282 --> 47:51.284
The Statue of Liberty is kaput.

47:51.369 --> 47:54.746
-"The Statue of Liberty is kaput."
-...kaput.

47:54.830 --> 47:56.623
That's disconcerting.

47:59.669 --> 48:01.253
Take the second left...

48:01.337 --> 48:04.631
Your father was circumcised
by my rabbi, you prick!

48:04.715 --> 48:07.801
Private Ryan, James,
probably misdropped with the 1 01 .

48:07.885 --> 48:09.886
-Got that?
-Cover!

48:17.520 --> 48:18.937
Go!

48:42.920 --> 48:45.130
-You sadistic fucking animals!
-Get down.

48:45.214 --> 48:48.300
They know we're not in direct contact.
They're gonna single out the runners.

48:48.384 --> 48:50.093
Yeah. Why do they
keep shooting him up like that?

48:50.177 --> 48:52.804
Long as his lungs have breath in them,
he still carries the message.

48:52.888 --> 48:54.597
-We'd do the same thing.
-No, we wouldn't!

48:54.682 --> 48:57.642
-Wade! Get them ready to travel.
-Yes, sir.

48:57.727 --> 48:59.602
-Boyd!
-Come on!

48:59.687 --> 49:02.439
Try again. See if you can let
Captain Hamill know we're coming.

49:02.523 --> 49:05.108
What's the rest of Neuville look like?

49:05.192 --> 49:07.569
Next block's got two-storey buildings,
both sides of the street.

49:07.653 --> 49:09.029
-There's a lot of windows.
-...copy? Over.

49:09.113 --> 49:11.489
And then there's a wide open square
with pretty good cover on the left.

49:11.574 --> 49:13.825
-Show me.
-Sarge, hold right here.

49:13.909 --> 49:15.327
Yes, sir!

49:19.749 --> 49:22.375
All right. Let's stay out of this enfilade
and use the buildings.

49:22.460 --> 49:23.585
Try a left hook.

49:23.669 --> 49:25.420
Shoot and scoot,
two of yours, two of mine.

49:25.504 --> 49:27.964
Hastings, Goldman, up front!

49:29.133 --> 49:31.926
-Reiben, Caparzo. Fundamentals.
-They're still jamming us.

49:32.011 --> 49:34.637
Short runs. High and low at the corners.

49:34.722 --> 49:37.182
lt's gonna be tight.
Be prepared for close contact.

49:37.266 --> 49:39.100
-Go. Upham.
-Yes, sir.

49:39.185 --> 49:41.311
-You stay with Sergeant Horvath.
-Stay right here.

49:41.395 --> 49:45.023
l'll wear him like underwear, Captain!
Stay with me.

49:53.157 --> 49:54.616
All right, past the end
of the block to the left.

49:54.700 --> 49:55.825
Those are the gates to the square.

49:55.910 --> 49:57.202
Good.

50:05.211 --> 50:07.003
Reiben, where's the captain from?

50:07.088 --> 50:09.255
You figure that one out,
you got yourself a nice prize.

50:09.340 --> 50:10.965
300 bucks, last l heard.

50:11.050 --> 50:14.302
Company's got a pool.
5 bucks gets you in.

50:18.724 --> 50:20.058
Easy.

50:21.644 --> 50:25.522
lt's around this corner.
Defilade right up to those gates.

50:26.690 --> 50:29.109
Somebody must know where he's from,
what he did for a living.

50:29.193 --> 50:31.027
l've been with him
since Kasserine Pass,

50:31.112 --> 50:32.278
but l don't have a clue.

50:32.363 --> 50:34.155
My ankles are killing me.

50:34.240 --> 50:37.200
l'll need a wheelchair
before this war is over.

50:37.284 --> 50:39.744
Oh, that's it. Oh, my God.

50:39.829 --> 50:43.081
Got ankles like an old woman.
Like an old...

50:43.165 --> 50:44.874
Oh, God.

50:46.627 --> 50:49.796
Reiben, so, you don't even know
where he went to school?

50:49.880 --> 50:51.089
Captain didn't go to school.

50:51.173 --> 50:54.342
They assembled him at OCS
out of spare body parts of dead Gls.

50:54.427 --> 50:55.802
You gotta pay attention to detail.

50:55.886 --> 50:57.804
l know exactly where he's from
and exactly what he did

50:57.888 --> 51:00.140
'cause l pay attention to detail.

51:00.224 --> 51:03.685
Hey, Upham,
careful you don't step in the bullshit.

51:09.024 --> 51:11.401
-Do it.
-Thunder!

51:11.485 --> 51:14.612
Thunder, or we will fire on you!

51:23.998 --> 51:27.417
Upham, tell them to show themselves.

51:38.721 --> 51:41.764
Ask them if they know
where the Germans are.

51:45.895 --> 51:48.771
-What's he saying?
-Something about the children.

51:49.815 --> 51:52.317
-They want us to take the children.
-No, no, no. We can't take the kids.

51:52.401 --> 51:54.068
We can't take the kids. We can't!

51:54.153 --> 51:57.405
We can't take the kids! No!

52:00.284 --> 52:01.451
They think they'll be safe with us.

52:01.535 --> 52:03.703
lt's not gonna be
safe when they're with us!

52:03.787 --> 52:07.832
-lt's okay. lt's okay.
-Are you nuts? Listen to the captain!

52:07.917 --> 52:11.711
-Are you nuts? Listen to the captain!
-They think they'll be safe with us, sir.

52:12.004 --> 52:15.298
Caparzo! Put that kid back!

52:15.758 --> 52:17.050
lt's okay.

52:17.134 --> 52:20.386
-Caparzo! Put that little girl back!
-lt's okay. lt's okay. lt's okay.

52:20.471 --> 52:23.515
Caparzo, give that kid back now!

52:23.599 --> 52:27.644
Upham, how do you say, "lt's okay"?
l can't. She reminds me of my niece, sir.

52:27.728 --> 52:29.687
Caparzo, get the kid back up there!

52:29.772 --> 52:31.105
Captain, the decent thing to do

52:31.190 --> 52:33.399
is to at least take her down
the road to the next town.

52:33.484 --> 52:36.736
We're not here to do the decent thing!
We're here to follow fucking orders!

52:36.820 --> 52:39.197
Sarge, take this goddamn kid!

52:39.949 --> 52:42.116
Cover! Cover!

52:51.418 --> 52:54.337
God damn it! Where'd that come from?

52:56.131 --> 52:59.592
He was on the ground
before we heard the shot.

53:04.348 --> 53:06.266
That's where l'd be.

53:08.143 --> 53:09.352
l didn't see it.

53:09.436 --> 53:12.272
Four hundred fifty yards, Captain.
Maybe a shade under.

53:12.356 --> 53:16.609
l wouldn't venture out there, fellas!
This sniper's got talent!

53:21.073 --> 53:24.534
Please don't cry. l'm gonna take you
back to your mama and papa.

53:24.618 --> 53:26.828
Please don't cry. Come on.

53:30.082 --> 53:31.499
Carpy.

53:42.595 --> 53:44.929
-Captain.
-Hold on, Caparzo.

53:46.348 --> 53:48.516
Help me up. l can walk. l can walk.

53:48.642 --> 53:50.768
Caparzo, stay still!

54:02.197 --> 54:04.490
Two clicks, left wind.

54:08.162 --> 54:09.495
Fish!

54:17.504 --> 54:20.298
Captain, can you see him
from there? How is he?

54:20.382 --> 54:22.342
Wade, you stay put.

54:22.468 --> 54:24.636
Where's he shot, Captain?

54:26.472 --> 54:29.015
-Captain, can you see him from there?
-You stay there!

54:29.141 --> 54:32.769
Damn it, stay down!
What's the matter with you?

54:32.853 --> 54:36.606
Am l gonna take care of you
if you get hit? Huh?

54:36.690 --> 54:39.942
-Fish, come over here.
-Carpy, put your head down.

54:40.027 --> 54:43.196
Why can't you put your head down?

54:50.871 --> 54:53.706
O my God, l trust in thee.

54:53.832 --> 54:55.833
Let me not be ashamed.

54:56.710 --> 54:59.545
Let not my enemies triumph over me.

55:09.348 --> 55:11.015
Copy it.

55:11.100 --> 55:13.434
Copy it and send it for me.

55:13.519 --> 55:15.978
Carpy, you're gonna send it yourself.
Put it down!

55:16.063 --> 55:19.357
-lt's got blood!
-l see it. Carpy, l see it.

55:23.904 --> 55:28.032
lt's to my dad. lt's got blood on it, Fish.

55:56.061 --> 55:58.604
We got him. Stay down.

56:07.322 --> 56:11.534
-How bad is it?
-Chest, maybe lung shot.

56:26.967 --> 56:29.510
Get that 30 up the street!

56:34.308 --> 56:35.558
Detail!

56:35.642 --> 56:37.727
-Clear up!
-Clear down!

56:53.368 --> 56:56.287
That's why we can't take children.

57:02.336 --> 57:05.922
Sergeant Horvath, do an ammo check.

57:06.006 --> 57:09.675
Upham, canteens. Fill them up.

57:10.260 --> 57:12.053
-Sergeant Hill.
-Yes, sir.

57:12.137 --> 57:16.516
Gather your men. We'll form up
at the northwest corner of the square.

57:16.600 --> 57:18.267
-Jackson!
-Sir.

57:18.352 --> 57:23.147
Mellish, check the tower,
hustle back here. Right now. Go!

57:34.993 --> 57:36.619
Fuck Ryan.

57:47.130 --> 57:49.549
-Thunder!
-Flash!

57:49.633 --> 57:51.175
Come on in.

57:55.973 --> 57:58.224
Hey, guys, we're looking
for Captain Hamill.

57:58.308 --> 58:00.059
Somewhere down there
across the square.

58:00.143 --> 58:01.435
Across the square.

58:01.520 --> 58:04.105
Go easy. Watch for snipers.

58:04.690 --> 58:06.440
Sit down.

58:23.000 --> 58:25.585
Jimmy T, go find Captain Hamill,
bring him in here.

58:25.669 --> 58:27.003
What? Up there?

58:27.087 --> 58:29.839
How the hell should l know?
Would you go look, please?

58:29.923 --> 58:31.883
Thank you, you moron.

58:33.260 --> 58:34.844
All right.

58:34.928 --> 58:38.389
You guys just flake out here for a while.

58:40.350 --> 58:43.811
Let me get this goddamn
hitchhiker out of my boot.

58:53.780 --> 58:55.615
Drop your weapons!
Drop your weapons!

58:55.699 --> 58:58.910
-Drop them now!
-Drop the fucking weapons!

59:01.747 --> 59:05.791
-l'll shoot you! l'll shoot you!
-Drop! Drop! Drop them!

59:08.295 --> 59:10.630
Now! Put them down!

59:25.729 --> 59:27.146
Clear up!

59:32.444 --> 59:36.155
-Shit. Shit!
-Clear up!

59:37.616 --> 59:39.158
Clear down!

59:51.129 --> 59:54.882
-Enough to make you old.
-Let's hope so.

01:00:05.852 --> 01:00:07.353
Fred Hamill, Pathfinders, 1 01 st.

01:00:07.437 --> 01:00:10.398
John Miller, 2nd Rangers. Thank you.

01:00:12.317 --> 01:00:13.943
